tamps with known offsets. MOCK-HIDE: Nothing hides; the sort function's behavior is fully observable with controlled inputs. LLM-DEP: Deterministic. MULTI-STEP: No. REJECTION-GATE for Integration: the 'clock skew' concern is about offsetting timestamps in input data, not about synchronising real clocks across processes.","test_description":"Build a set of log entries with timestamps deliberately out-of-order by up to 450ms (within skew budget) across two synthetic services. Call the timeline-sort function and assert the output is in strictly ascending causal order. Also assert that entries differing by exactly 500ms are handled without swapping incorrectly.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.74,"Integration":0.21,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"A latency spike (p99 above 3x the baseline) is detected and flagged in the anomaly report.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"MOCK-MISS: The failure mode is a statistical computation bug — wrong p99 calculation, wrong baseline, wrong 3x threshold comparison. All of these live inside a single detection function over a numeric dataset. REAL-INFRA: No I/O needed; latency values are plain numbers. MOCK-HIDE: Nothing to mock. LLM-DEP: Deterministic math. MULTI-STEP: No. REJECTION-GATE for Integration: 'flagged in the anomaly report' is an output step, but the core failure (undetected spike) lives in the detector, not in the report formatter; a unit test can assert the detector returns a flagged result.","test_description":"Provide two datasets: a baseline distribution and a spike distribution where the p99 is exactly 3.1x the baseline p99. Call the anomaly detector with both and assert it returns a flag. Then provide a dataset where p99 is 2.9x baseline and assert no flag is raised. Edge-case: verify the threshold is inclusive (exactly 3.0x triggers a flag).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.65,"Integration":0.3,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Malformed JSON log entries are skipped without crashing the pipeline, and the count of skipped entries is reported.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: The failure mode is not in the parser alone — it is whether the exception from parsing propagates up and crashes the pipeline, and whether the skip count is correctly accumulated and surfaced in the final report. This is a module-boundary failure: parser → pipeline orchestrator → report emitter. A unit test on the parser returning None does not verify the pipeline survives or that the count reaches the report. REAL-INFRA: No OS/network needed; in-process module wiring suffices. MOCK-HIDE: Mocking the parser would hide whether the real parser exception is caught upstream. LLM-DEP: Deterministic. MULTI-STEP: No. REJECTION-GATE for System: no subprocess, real filesystem, or network I/O is required to expose this failure.","test_description":"Wire the real parser, pipeline orchestrator, and report emitter together in-process. Feed a stream of 10 entries where 3 are invalid JSON strings. Assert the pipeline returns normally (no exception), the output report contains exactly 7 processed entries, and the skipped-entry count in the report equals 3.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.18,"Integration":0.68,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The tool handles a burst of 10,000 log entries per second without dropping entries or falling behind.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"MOCK-MISS: Throughput failures (dropped entries, queue overflow, backpressure breakdown) emerge from real I/O and OS scheduling, not from in-process data structure logic alone. REAL-INFRA: The tool 'ingests' logs — in a real deployment this means reading from files, stdin, or a stream. True burst behavior (OS buffer limits, file descriptor scheduling, real timer resolution) only manifests with actual I/O. An in-process test injecting a list at unbounded speed measures data structure speed, not real ingestion throughput. MOCK-HIDE: A mocked I/O layer always delivers entries instantly, hiding real backpressure failures. LLM-DEP: Deterministic. MULTI-STEP: No. REJECTION-GATE for Agentic: no AI/ML output involved. REJECTION-GATE for Workflow: single pipeline pass, not multiple agentic steps.","test_description":"Spawn the tool as a real subprocess (or invoke it against a real file/pipe). Feed a pre-generated file of 50,000 well-formed JSON log entries and time the ingestion. Assert that all 50,000 entries appear in the output (zero dropped), total wall-clock time stays within the 5-second budget implied by the 10k/s spec, and no error or warning about falling behind is emitted.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.3,"System":0.62,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.03}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":10003,"cache_read_input_tokens":3199,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":10003},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6c74bcf9-38c2-4ca8-8465-e11e98edc876","uuid":"49e24573-0f5f-434e-a321-5fea23a97d68"}
